Description: Figure; bone; carved in relief; nude woman walking to right; she wears a loose drape wrapped around her and carries a tympanum(?) in her right hand; another tympanum(?) between her feet.
Bibliographic references: Petrie at al 1915 / Heliopolis, Kafr Ammar and Shurafa (p. 43, pl. L.2)
Acquisition name: Donated by: British School of Archaeology, Egypt
Acquisition notes: Register says found c.6 miles south of Helouan.
